## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of recent empirical studies on the impact of dress codes. Much of the information is based on opinion pieces and anecdotal evidence, which may not fully capture the complexities of the issue. Additionally, the cultural context of dress codes can vary significantly, and this report primarily reflects perspectives from the United States. Further research could explore the impact of dress codes in different cultural and educational settings.